<HEADLINE> Gathering Held to Mark Women's Day </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 7 (Xinhua) -- Hu Jintao, Member of the Standing
Committee of the Political Bureau of the Communist Party of China
(CPC) Central Committee, joined 1,800 women representing all
circles in a grand gathering here to mark the March 8
International Women's Day.
</P>
<P>
Chen Muhua, Vice-Chairman of the National People's Congress
Standing Committee, made a speech at the gathering sending festive
greetings to all women in the country and the world. She thanked
all those who have supported the cause of women's development.
</P>
<P>
The equality between men and women is the final goal of the
mankind, and to protect women is an important symbol of the human
civilization, said Chen, who is also president of the All-China
Women's Federation.
</P>
<P>
She expressed her hope that women deputies to the National
People's Congress and female members of the National Committee of
the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference would
display their level of participating in the deliberation and
administration of state affairs. Both the NPC and the CPPCC
National Committee are now in session in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Also present at the gathering were women leaders including Wu
Yi, Lei Jieqiong, Peng Peiyun, Qian Zhengying and He Luli.
</P>
</TEXT>
