<HEADLINE> Egypt Condemns Violence in Kosovo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, March 7 (Xinhua) -- Egypt said Saturday the escalating
conflicts in the troubled Kosovo province, Yugoslavia, may lead to
a "virtual explosion" in the region.
</P>
<P>
A Foreign Ministry statement condemned the killing of many
civilians in the violence which broke out last weekend.
</P>
<P>
At least 45 Albanians and six Serb police were killed in Kosovo
since an armed conflict between ethnic Albanian separatists and
police took place on March 1.
</P>
<P>
The statement urged the world community to help hold a dialog
between the authorities in Belgrade and Kosovo to settle the issue
and to exert all needed efforts to achieve justice and stability.
</P>
<P>
Ethnic Albanians, who account for 90 percent of the population
in Kosovo, have been seeking independence from Yugoslavia since
1981. 
</P>
</TEXT>
