<HEADLINE> AL Chief to Visit Algeria on March 10 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, March 7 (Xinhua) -- Arab League Secretary General Esmat
Abdel-Meguid said Saturday he will pay a three-day visit to
Algiers on Tuesday to discuss regional issues with Algerian
leaders.
</P>
<P>
He is expected to discuss with Algerian President Liamine
Zeroual and other high-ranking Algerian officials on the stalled
Mideast peace process, the arms inspection crisis in Iraq and
efforts to effect an Arab reconciliation.
</P>
<P>
Quoted by Egypt's Middle East News Agency, he hailed the
changes towards democracy underway in Algeria and the multi-party
system being followed there.
</P>
<P>
Algeria has urged the holding of regular Arab summits to
demonstrate Arab solidarity and, in particular, to combat
terrorism which panicked the northern African country over the
past six years.
</P>
<P>
Muslim insurgency has killed an estimated 75,000 people in
Algeria since 1992, when the government canceled legislative
elections the Islamic Salvation Front was tipped to win. 
</P>
</TEXT>
