<HEADLINE> President: Iran Favors Mutual Respect in Relations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, March 7 (Xinhua) -- Iranian President Mohammad Khatami
Saturday reiterated that Iran favors international relations that
are based on mutual respect.
</P>
<P>
"The Islamic Republic of Iran seeks to expand relations with
countries which observe the principle of mutual respect," Khatami
told reporters after a welcoming ceremony for Belarussian
President Alexander Lukashenko.
</P>
<P>
He said that to ease international tensions figures prominently
in Iran's foreign policy.
</P>
<P>
"Broad relations between Iran and Belarus are not detrimental
to any other country and the two countries' relations based on
mutual respect can help the cause of peace and stability in the
region," the Iranian president said.
</P>
<P>
Tehran and Minsk are intent on expanding bilateral ties in
political, economic, cultural and scientific fields, he said.
</P>
<P>
The Belarussian president voiced Minsk's readiness to further
promote cooperation with Iran, saying that "Minsk-Tehran
negotiations are constructive and subject to no limitations."
</P>
<P>
He stressed that Belarus pursues an independent foreign policy
free from foreign powers' domination, saying that "our policy is
similar to that of the Islamic Republic of Iran in this respect."
</P>
<P>
Lukashenko arrived here Friday night for an official visit,
during which the two countries will sign a number of cooperation
agreements. 
</P>
</TEXT>
