<HEADLINE> Ghanaian Man Freezes to Death in Mortuary Fridge </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, March 7 (Xinhua) -- Ghanaian businessman James
Maccarthy was frozen to death after being left in a mortuary
refrigerator by relatives who mistook him for being dead, a
report from Accra, capital of Ghana said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The Mirror paper was quoted as saying that Maccarthy, aged 43,
was found dead early this week in a refrigerator in a police
hospital mortuary, where he had been left by relatives.
</P>
<P>
He fell into a coma while being driven to the hospital by his
relatives, who put him at the mortuary instead of at the
emergency ward, and hence the misfortune, the paper added.
</P>
<P>
The businessman had bruises to his face, neck, hands and legs
suggesting that he had struggled to get out of the mortuary
drawer before he died of cold, said the paper. 
</P>
