private sector is our hope and we need assistance to sustain
peace and to develop our natural resources, banking systems etc."
</P>
<P>
The 10-member U.S. team, led by President Bill Clinton's
special envoy Howard Jeter, arrived in Monrovia Thursday on the
first such visit since Taylor's inauguration last August.
</P>
<P>
"We bring a message of goodwill and we are here for very
intensive discussions with the government and other individuals,"
Jeter said on arrival. 
