<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, March 7 (Xinhua) -- Two Tanzanians have died,
while the other two of the same family have been sent to
hospital, after they ate porridge suspected to be poisonous, the
police said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The Regional Police Commander Alfred Geww, named the two
people who died of the poisonous porridge Friday at Goba Village
in Dar es Salaam as Mpuya Mwandu, 30, and Juma Lushingo, 23.
</P>
<P>
One survivor, Mange, admitted that the deceased Mpuya Mwandu
was preparing the porridge with traditional medicine.
</P>
<P>
"Mpuya was unable to have sex, so he cooked the porridge with
the soup of some roots given by traditional healers in the belief
that it would cure his impotence," Mange said.
</P>
<P>
"We all abandoned the meal in a few minutes, except for Mpuya
who continued eating until he was satisfied," he said.
</P>
<P>
Mpuya fell down suddenly after 10 minutes and so did Juma
later. Both of them died soon.
</P>
<P>
The police are still investigating the specific reason for the
incident. 
</P>
