change happening in many African countries. Since 1993, 12
African stock markets have been opened to foreign investments and
the trade volumes in those stock markets have risen six-fold from
600 million U.S. Dollars to 4.5 billion Dollars.
</P>
<P>
According to the release, the forum is the first of what will
be a series of conferences highlighting Africa as an investment
opportunity area for the international business community.
</P>
<P>
The objective of this and subsequent fora is to examine and
debate ways in which economic investment can be promoted, the
release said. 
