<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 16 GMT, March 8 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN -- U.S. Secretary of State Madeleine Albright and her
German counterpart Klaus Kinkel Sunday agreed to act swiftly to
intervene in the Kosovo issue and to force Belgrade to make
concession on it.
</P>
<P>
After meeting Kinkel in Bonn on Sunday, Albright warned at a
news conference that Washington would stop moves to ease sanctions
against Belgrade unless violence stopped.
</P>
<P>
"The time to stop killings is now before it spreads. The way
to do it is to take an immediate action against Belgrade to ensure
that it pay the price for the damages already done and to
encourage it to finally resolve the problems in Kosovo," Albright
said.
</P>
<P>
Kinkel also stressed that "everything must be done to ensure
that another awful conflagration do not explode in Europe."
(Germany-US-Kosovo)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM, March 8 (Xinhua) -- Palestinian Security forces
have informed Israel that they uncovered an underground workshop
for making rifles in Gaza, Israel Radio reported Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinians said that hundreds of rifles have already
been manufactured by the factory.
</P>
<P>
But Israeli security forces said they believed the number of
rifles made there was not as large as that reported by the
Palestinians.
</P>
<P>
There was no report about who operated the factory and whether
some suspects have been arrested.
</P>
<P>
Israel has been insisting that its next troop pullback from
the West Bank is contingent on the implementation of the
Palestinian commitments to fight against terrorists.
(Palestine-Rifle Workshop)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BAGHDAD -- Iraqi Oil Minister Amir Mohammed Rasheed said on
Saturday that Iraq wants lifting of U.N. sanctions instead of the
oil-for-food deal, a very temporary measure.
</P>
<P>
In an exclusive interview with Xinhua, Rasheed said
oil-for-food deal under U.N. Security Council resolution 986,
which allows Iraq to sell limited amount of oil to buy food and
medicine, was temporary measure supposed to be for only six months.
</P>
<P>
However, he said, the deal has existed for three years instead
of six months.
</P>
<P>
"We work with it, we facilitate its implementation, but it is
temporary measure. The proper measure is the lifting of all
sanctions, which we deserve fully," he said.
</P>
<P>
Rasheed, top negotiator in talks with the U.N. Special
Commission charged of disarming Iraq of its weapons of mass
destruction, said the United States intended to make oil-for-food
deal a sort of permanent measure, so that iraq can only buy
consuming items. (Iraq-Oil Minister) 
</P>
</TEXT>
