<HEADLINE> Pontoni Suspended for Cocaine </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, March 8 (Xinhua) -- Daniele Pontoni, former world
cyclo-cross champion, was suspended for six months by the Italian
Cycling Federation on Sunday after testing positive for cocaine.
</P>
<P>
The federation's disciplinary committee said the ban would
begin as soon as the rider was notified of the decision.
</P>
<P>
Pontoni tested positive after winning a race at Parabiago near
Milan on January 11. A second drug test confirmed his urine sample
contained the substance.
</P>
<P>
It was unclear if the ban would be recognised by the world
governing body. 
</P>
