<HEADLINE> Bayi Rockets Enter Semi-Final at China Basketball League </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 8 (Xinhua) -- The Bayi Rockets trounced the
Jinan Army Pegasus 107-64 in Xian Sunday to become the first team
to enter the semi-finals of the China basketball league after
winning the first round best-of-three play-offs.
</P>
<P>
The three time champions, ranked first in the regular season,
beat the 8th-ranked Army opponents 75-65 in thisseason's play-off
first meet last week on the road.
</P>
<P>
Wang Zhishi scored 21 points and grabbed nine rebounds for the
Bayi team, which led the first half 63-34 at the lopsided home
game.
</P>
<P>
The Bayi will face the winners between the Beijing Ducks and
the Shanghai Sharks in the semi-finals.
</P>
<P>
The Sharks revenged their 52-76 home defeat last week to
outplay the Ducks 81-59 in Beijing on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Croatian Vaidas had a game-high 36 points and 16 rebounds to
lead the Sharks, which took the advantage after a eight-minute
behind and ended the first half 44-31.
</P>
<P>
The Ducks, led by Bateer's 22 points and 12 rebounds, closed
the gap to 39-44 with a 10-0 run with three minutes into the
second half, but only scored seven points in the following seven
minutes when Shanghai used a 16-7 spur for a 60-46 lead.
</P>
<P>
In Shengyang, The Liaoning Hunters edged the Guangdong Tigers
74-72, also tying their best-of-three play-offs.
</P>
<P>
Wu Naiqiong contributed 15 points and six rebounds to lead all
Hunters' starters with double figures in scoring.
</P>
<P>
Ji Chonglong hit 17 points for the Tigers, which beat the
Hunters 78-68 last week.
</P>
<P>
In Jinan, Gong Xiaobing scored 30 points and added eight
rebounds to lead the Shandong Flaming Bulls over the Jiangsu
Dragons 73-52, forcing both sides into their third game.
</P>
<P>
The all three third games in the first round play-offs will be
played on Wednesday with winners into the semi-finals. 
</P>
</TEXT>
