<HEADLINE> HK CPPCC Members Urge Taiwan to Respond to Negotiation Appeal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 8 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong members of the Chinese
People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC) National
Committee, China's top advisory body, expressed the hope that the
Taiwan authorities would respond quickly to the mainland's appeal
to start cross-Strait political negotiations under the "one China"
principle.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with Xinhua, Sze Chi Qing, chairman of the
board of directors of Hong Kong Hang Tung Resources Holding
Limited and a member of the CPPCC National Committee, said Hong
Kong has maintained stability and prosperity after its return to
the motherland under the "one country, two systems" principle.
Macao's return is close at hand. "Now is a good time to make
progress toward the reunification of the motherland," he said.
</P>
<P>
Sze Cheung Pang, another CPPCC National Committee member and a
Hong Kong businessman, expressed regret that the Taiwan
authorities have not responded earnestly and positively to the
eight-point proposal made by President Jiang Zemin.
</P>
<P>
The Taiwan authorities now have again turned down negotiation
offers on the ground that they are opposed to "preconditions." The
key to developing cross-Strait relations at the present stage is
to urge the Taiwan authorities to come to the negotiation table,
Sze said.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that, if there should be a precondition or a
premise for cross-Strait negotiations, that is the principle of
"one China."
</P>
<P>
"The 'one China' principle is the key to whether or not
cross-Strait relations can develop smoothly and a peaceful
reunification of the motherland can be accomplished," he said.
</P>
<P>
Member Liang Hin-ying, president of the Chinese Manufacturers'
Association in Hong Kong, said Hong Kong has been serving as a
bridge in promoting cooperation and exchanges across the Taiwan
Strait. Hong Kong CPPCC members will contribute more to the
peaceful reunification of the motherland, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
