<HEADLINE> American and Czech Set Women's Pole Vault Indoor Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BERLIN, March 8 (Xinhua) -- Both Stacy Dragila of the United
States and Daniela Bartova of the Czech Republic leapt over 4.48
meters to share the women's pole vault world record Sunday at an
indoor meet in Sindelfingen, Germany.
</P>
<P>
Dragila, the indoor world champion, jumpped over 4.48 meters in
her second attempt before Bartova overcame the same height in her
third.
</P>
<P>
The indoor world record was the fourth time set in three days
with Bartova breaking twice.
</P>
<P>
Bartova, a former gymnast, claimed 4.46 in Berlin Friday,
slicing the previous mark of 4.45 meters, created by Anzhela
Balachonova of Ukraine only five-day fresh.
</P>
<P>
Australian Emma George, outdoor world record holder of 4.57,
bettered the record one day later to 4.47 in Adelaide, Australia.
</P>
