<HEADLINE> American Mannino Collects Third Downhill Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, March 8 (Xinhua) -- Two-time men's Alpine skiing
downhill champion Greg Mannino of the United States won his third
straight gold medal in the Winter Paralympic Games in Nagano,
Japan, on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
His compatriot Christopher Waddell and John Davis also won
their categories to bring home two more golds, while Hans Burn and
Rolf Heinzmann both snatched two for Switzerland and James
Lawrence Paterson one for Australia in Shiga Kogen.
</P>
<P>
It was Mannino's 11th Paralympic medal and fifth gold overall,
including one silver in the Olympic demonstration giant slalom in
Calgary in 1988.
</P>
<P>
Russia swept four gold medals in the Nordic skiing
cross-country event, while Finland wrapped three titles and Norway
two at the Snow Harp in Hakuba.
</P>
<P>
In the ice sledge hockey at the Aqua Wing ice arena, Sweden
beat Estonia 6-3 in the preliminary Pool A competition.
</P>
<P>
After the fourth day of the competition, Norway topped the
standings with eight golds, five silvers and six bronzes, ahead of
Germany with 7-8-5, Japan 5-9-5 and Switzerland 5-0-2. 
</P>
</TEXT>
