<HEADLINE> Li Ruihuan Calls for Better Care for Masses of People </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 8 (Xinhua) -- Li Ruihuan, a Standing Committee
member of the Political Bureau of the Communist Party of China
(CPC) Central Committee, today urged leading officials at all
levels to concern themselves with the masses of people and do more
in-depth investigations and studies.
</P>
<P>
Joining in a panel discussion on Premier Li's Government Work
Report with deputies to the Ninth National People's Congress (NPC)
from Tianjin Municipalities, Li cited the report as "practical"
and "inspiring".
</P>
<P>
"The people are the mainstay in the reform and opening-up, and
we will accomplish nothing without tapping their wisdom, strength
and talents," said Li, who is present as an NPC deputy from Tianjin.
</P>
<P>
At present, the overall level of China's economic growth is not
high, and a host of problems have cropped up during the shift of
economic mechanism. Therefore, some urban and rural people are
leading a relatively hard life, and there is a growing number of
laid-off workers in cities, Li said.
</P>
<P>
In addition, he noted, corruption, unfair income distribution,
bureaucratic work style, formalism and frauds among some officials
have caused complaints from the masses of people.
</P>
<P>
In this sense, he warned officials of not losing their position
on the minds of the people they worked for.
</P>
<P>
While reform has greatly raised the overall living standards of
the residents, the interests of some people may be affected for
some time and, with the establishment of the market economy,
layoff and unemployment are inevitable, he said.
</P>
<P>
"We should not doubt the general orientation of the reform or
the people's will to carry it out simply because of some
problems that have emerged in the course of advancement, nor
should we ignore the people's practical difficulties under any
excuse," Li Ruihuan said.
</P>
<P>
"In view of China's present material conditions, the people's
basic livelihood can entirely be guaranteed," he said.
</P>
<P>
To fulfill the arduous tasks put forward by the Government Work
Report, officials at various levels should not be impetuous and
subjective, but free themselves from meetings and excessive social
activities and, go in for more investigations and studies instead.
</P>
</TEXT>
