<HEADLINE> Premier Calls for Tackling Problems in Small Firms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 8 (Xinhua) -- Premier Li Peng called on
governments at all levels to properly deal with problems faced by
numerous small and medium-sized enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Such enterprises constitute the majority of debt-ridden firms,
where most laid-off workers come from, the premier said.
</P>
<P>
Li made the call in a group discussion attended by Shandong
deputies to the National People's Congress (NPC), in session here
since last Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Li said large state firms dominate with economic strength while
small enterprises employ the majority of workers.
</P>
<P>
That is why governments at all levels must handle problems in
small enterprises well in state enterprise reform, he said.
</P>
<P>
Mixed ownership is conducive to the technical upgrading and
development of small and medium-sized enterprises, he said.
</P>
<P>
Li said accelerating the development of the service industry is
an important way to create more job opportunities for laid-off
workers.
</P>
<P>
"Textile and other light industrial factories use relatively
backward equipment and their products lack competitiveness, but
most of them are located at precious downtown sites, a great
advantage for them to develop services, he said.
</P>
<P>
The premier also suggested developing community services as a
way to provide jobs for laid-off workers.  
</P>
