<DOCNO> XIE19980308.0060 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Profile: Xiao Hong, Designer of Macao SAR Regional Flag &AMP; Emblem </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 8 (Xinhua) -- It was three years after the
regional flag and emblem of the Macao Special Administrative
Region (SAR) was adopted that its 38-year-old designer, Xiao Hong,
made his first trip to Macao.
</P>
<P>
"When I was working on my design, I had no idea about what
Macao resembled; and the only material I had got for reference was
a 600-word tourist guide to it," recalled the astute and
lean-faced Xiao, now a deputy to the Ninth National People's
Congress (NPC), China's top legislature that is in session here
since last Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Xiao, a professor of arts and crafts from central China's Henan
University, attributed his success to the longing for the early
accomplishment of China's reunification.
</P>
<P>
"Sensory appeal works in artistic creation, but what's more
important is the input of an artist's true feelings and
dedication," Xiao said.
</P>
<P>
In 1992, Xiao overwhelmed over thousands of entrants to win the
top prize of a national contest, and his works became the best
design for the regional flag and emblem of the Macao SAR, which
will be officially founded on December 20 next year with Macao's
return to China.
</P>
<P>
He was then asked by the Drafting Committee for the Basic Law
of the Macao SAR to further improve his designs until they were
approved through examinations during the First Session of the
Eighth NPC in early 1993.
</P>
<P>
Therefore, Xiao became one of the most popular figures in the
163-member delegation from Henan Province at the ongoing NPC
session after his fellow lawmakers learned about his background.
</P>
<P>
"I have for long known that it was a young designer from our
province who created the Macao SAR's regional flag and emblem, but
I didn't expect to meet him during this session," one Henan deputy
exclaimed.
</P>
<P>
Xiao said he was looking forward to the grand ceremony marking
Macao's return to the motherland, at which the flag and emblem he
designed will add to the solemn and jubilant mood on the occasion.
</P>
<P>
"That will be the happiest moment in my life," he said
excitedly.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
