<HEADLINE> Palestinian Security Forces Uncover Rifle Workshop </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, March 8 (Xinhua) -- Palestinian Security forces
have informed Israel that they uncovered an underground workshop
for making rifles in Gaza, Israel Radio reported Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinians said that hundreds of rifles have already
been manufactured by the factory.
</P>
<P>
But Israeli security forces said they believed the number of
rifles made there was not as large as that reported by the
Palestinians.
</P>
<P>
There was no report about who operated the factory and whether some
suspects have been arrested.
</P>
<P>
Last Thursday, Palestinian security forces arrested some
members of a Hamas terrorist cell in the West Bank city of Nablus,
who reportedly had been planning a terrorist attack somewhere in
central Israel.
</P>
<P>
Israel has been insisting that its next troop pullback from
the West Bank is contingent on the implementation of the
Palestinian commitments to fight against terrorists.
</P>
<P>
Frequent terrorist attacks against Israel in recent years have
seriously hold up the Israeli-Palestinian peace process which has
been stalled since Israel began construction of a Jewish settlement
in Arab East Jerusalem last March. 
</P>
