<HEADLINE> US Delegation Comments On China's Village Election (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Liu Guodong, a section chief in charge of grass-roots political
power at Jilin's Civil Affairs Bureau, said that the village
committee election is important because it helps form the basic
procedures of democratic elections, with its secret ballet, direct
elections, choosing from a number of candidates, and counting
ballots in public.
</P>
<P>
Mobile poll boxes have been used to help the elderly and the
disabled, and boxes are the responsibility of specially designated
people, whose job is to see that the voting process stays legal.
</P>
<P>
Dr. Pastor said that the process was handled in a very good
manner, and that, even in the United States, problems often occur
with mobile boxes. He said that, to ensure impartial and fair
election results, a good method is to ask both the winner and
loser of the election to sign the election results sheet.
</P>
<P>
He told Xinhua that what impressed him the most is
Chinese officials' desire to work with people to find better ways
to reach the common goal of mankind, of turning the desire for
democracy into actual democracy, but that he was impressed by the
hard work in the village elections and the fair competition to
choose leaders that people really believe in. 
</P>
