<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> NPC Deputies Favors Policy on Renminbi's Stable Exchange Rate </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 8 (Xinhua) -- Deputies to the Ninth National
People's Congress (NPC) in session here voiced their endorsement
to the policy of maintaining a stable exchange rate of Renminbi
(RMB).
</P>
<P>
They shared the view that many Asian nations were plunged into
a regional financial crisis and their financial system and
national economic growth suffered a hard blow, whereas China was
basically not affected in this regard and accorded a good momentum
for high economic growth with low inflation.
</P>
<P>
Many deputies voiced the hope that China will continue to
implement a stable financial policy.
</P>
<P>
Li Yining, an NPC deputy and a noted economist, held that RMB
should not be depreciated, nor is there any necessary to do so. If
the Chinese yuan is depreciated, it will aggravate the Southeast
Asian financial crisis and compel the related countries to
continue devaluating their currencies.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, he noted that the Reminbi's depreciation will have
an impact on China's absorption of investment from overseas as it
will cast a heavier burden on imports though it can stimulate
exports. Enterprises then will have a great pressure in repaying
foreign debts, he added.
</P>
<P>
Xie Qingjian, president of the Zhejiang Branch of the People's
Bank of China (PBC), said the maintenance of a stable RMB is of
great importance to the country's economic growth. With an
unstable currency value, a nation's economy is likely to
fluctuate, he noted. The reform on China's exchange system over
the years has proven successful and accords with the country's
actual conditions.
</P>
<P>
As China has a foreign currency reserve of 140 billion U.S.
dollars, it retained a steady economic growth with a low price
rise rate. All these make the people to confide still more in a
stable RMB exchange rate, Xie said.
</P>
<P>
Zhou Houjian, head of the Hi-Sense Group, a high-tech firm
based in the port city of Qingdao in east China's Shandong
Province, said, "the maintenance of a stable RMB exchange rate has
brought great benefits and provides a very favaorable outer
environment for new and high-tech enterprises."
</P>
<P>
Chan Yau-hing, an NPC deputy from the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (SAR) and chairman of the Asia Financial
Holdings, said that stable exchange rate of RMB is a matter of
concern in Hong Kong, as it benefits Hong Kong's current practice
of pegging its dollar with U.S. dollar and boosted the residents'
confidence in the HK SAR, which returned to the embrace of the
motherland eight months ago.
</P>
<P>
The international community is following closely with the
trends of development with the RMB, which shows that its stable
exchange rate plays a decisive role in stabilizing economic growth
in Asia and the world as a whole, he noted.
</P>
<P>
Deputies from industrial circles were unanimous that the
depreciation of currencies in neighboring countries will not
affect China's exports, especially its processing trade with
supplied materials.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, NPC deputies have also shown a firm support to the
decision of continuing to improve and intensify financial control
and supervision.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
