<HEADLINE> Export Fair Opens In Tianjin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, March 8 (Xinhua) -- An eight-day export fair opened
today in the north China port city of Tianjin.
</P>
<P>
About 2,000 Chinese and overseas business people and foreign
diplomats in China attended the opening ceremony of the fair,
which is sponsored by 12 provinces, municipalities and autonomous
regions in north, northwest and southwest China.
</P>
<P>
The fair will feature electric machinery, and light industry
products. A total of 434 Chinese factories attended with 570
booths.
</P>
<P>
There are also 20 overseas enterprises from the Republic of
Korea, Canada, Hong Kong and Taiwan regions taking part.
</P>
<P>
This is the ninth of its kind. Last year's was the most
successful so far, and had over 2,000 business people from 61
countries and regions, and the import and export contracts signed
at the fair were worth a total of 650 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
A State Economic and Trade Commission official said that the
fair helped promote regional trade, and 13 provinces did 16.63
billion US dollars in export business last year, 14.6 percent more
than for the previous year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
