<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tanzanian Govt Urged to Attack Theft of Electric </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, March 8 (Xinhua) -- A Tanzanian lawmaker has
urged the government to attack the rampant theft of electric
wires which has affected power supplies.
</P>
<P>
Theft of electric wires has forced the Pangani District
Hospital in the Tanga region on the border with Kenya to suspend
services due to power shortage, Mohamed Rished Abdallah, a member
of parliament, told reporters in Dar es Salaam Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The MP, who is from Pangani, said the electric wires which
were stolen in the region were sold in Kenya. Three incidents of
the same nature have been reported this year, according to the
Daily News.
</P>
<P>
Such criminal activities took place in remote areas in most
cases, said Rished, who advised the Tanzanian Electric Supply
Company (TANESCO) to install electric cables in densely populated
areas.
</P>
<P>
He also called on the government to collaborate with the
eastern and central African countries to attack the illegal
market of electric wires. 
</P>
</TEXT>
