<HEADLINE> Sorjaturong Secures WBC Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, March 8 (Xinhua) -- Saman Sorjaturong of Thailand
outplayed Japanese challenger Shire Yashiro to retain his World
Boxing Council junior flyweight champion title in Yokohama, Japan
on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Sorjaturong, 28, floored Yashiro with a left hook to the head
following a flurry of body blows before the bell rang at the end
of the third round.
</P>
<P>
The referee stopped the fight two minutes 20 seconds into the
fourth round of the scheduled 12 rounds when the defending
champion beat his 29-year-old rival with a technical knockout.
</P>
<P>
It was Sorjaturong's ninth defense of the title, therefore, his
professional record reached to 38 wins, one draw and two
losses. 
</P>
</TEXT>
