<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Chief Executive Departs for Germany, France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 8 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's Chief Executive Tung
Chee Hwa left here Sunday for a week-long visit to Germany and
France.
</P>
<P>
At a press conference at the airport, Tung said that he will
bring the message to the two European countries that "since the
return of Hong Kong (to China), everything is really going well,
that 'one country, two systems' is now solidly embedded, that the
pride and confidence level is high."
</P>
<P>
Only very recently, the German Chamber of Commerce conducted a
survey which showed close to 85 percent of the Germans here have
a great deal of confidence in Hong Kong, Tung noted.
</P>
<P>
Of course there are "pains and challenges brought about by the
currency turmoil around us", Tung admitted. But "we have been
doing very well in containing these challenges and I am sure we
will come out even better than before," he said.
</P>
<P>
The chief executive will be accompanied by Secretary for Trade
and Industry Denise Yue on the European trip.
</P>
<P>
Tung will spend two days in Germany, visiting Bonn and
Frankfurt. On his tentative agenda are meetings with Chancellor
Helmut Kohl and other government officials.
</P>
<P>
On his three-day visit to France, which includes visits to
Paris and Lyon, the Chief Executive will meet French President
Jacques Chirac and Prime Minister Lionel Jospin. 
</P>
</TEXT>
