<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice-Premier Calls for Readjusting Investment Structure </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 8 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier Zhu Rongji
today called for readjusting investment structure, cuting down
expenditures, and stopping construction of top-grade office
buildings and luxury hotels and overlapping projects.
</P>
<P>
At a penal discussion of NPC deputies from the northeast China
province of Liaoning to the on-going Ninth National People's
Congress, Zhu said China will strive to increase its investment in
capital construction projects, railways and highways,
telecommunications, environmental protection, new and high-tech
projects, technological upgrading at existing enterprises and
residential housing projects.
</P>
<P>
