<HEADLINE> About 160 Companies De-registered in Zambia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, March 8 (Xinhua) -- Zambia Revenue Authority (ZRA) has
de-registered 161 companies and business houses which have failed
to remit value added tax (VAT).
</P>
<P>
The Times of Zambia Sunday quoted ZRA public relations officer
Juliet Sibande as saying Saturday that the de-registeration is an
ongoing exercise.
</P>
<P>
Sibande said the de-registered firms should immediately
surrender their certificates to ZRA.
</P>
<P>
She warned that those who will be found using certificates
after they have been de-registered will be charged 10,000 penalty
units or 12 months imprisonment.
</P>
<P>
"The law of the land will take its course and those caught
would be fined 10,000 penalty units which is equivalent to a fine
of 1.8 million Kwacha (1300 U.S. Dollars) or imprisonment not
exceeding 12 months or both," said Sibanda.
</P>
<P>
She added that those who are using certificates after being
de-registered are stealing money from the government. 
</P>
