<HEADLINE> Beijing Maintains Good Public Security: Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 8 (Xinhua) -- Beijing is one of the world's
best cities with public security, director of the Beijing Public
Security Bureau Zhang Liangji said today.
</P>
<P>
"It is absurd for someone to say that the crime rate in Beijing
is high as in New York," said Zhang, who is attending the First
Session of the Ninth National People's Congress (NPC) as an NPC
deputy.
</P>
<P>
The number of criminal offenses has been on the decline, and
the capital's public security keeps improving, the director told
reporters.
</P>
<P>
With regard to some major cases, public security departments
have gone all out to step up investigations and prosecutions. Some
absurdities about some crime cases in Beijing spreading overseas
are untrue, he noted.
</P>
<P>
"Nevertheless, we cannot lower our guard as economic reform is
unfolding in a deep-going way," he said, adding that the flux of
immigrants from elsewhere in China imposed a pressure on public
security situation in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
In addition, hundreds of thousands of workers will have been
laid off by the year 2000. They might affect public security if
the problem is not handled appropriately, he said.
</P>
<P>
So there lies ahead the arduous task of cracking down on
drug-related crimes and organized crimes, Zhang said.
</P>
<P>
As China is in the primary stage of socialism, he explained,
crimes cannot be done away with overnight, and some cases might
be on rise sometimes," he said.
</P>
<P>
Quoted Premier Li as saying in his government work report on
Thursday,"It is entirely necessary to strengthen armed police, and
public security and state security departments," Zhang said that
"it is of major importance to maintain stability in Beijing as
China's capital city." 
</P>
</TEXT>
