<HEADLINE> Xinjiang People Aspire to Stability and Development: Official (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Moreover, he noted, Xinjiang has been receiving considerable
support from the central government and other areas of the
country.
</P>
<P>
A drinking water project completed last year enabled 4.5
million residents of various ethnic groups in Xinjiang to have
access to limpid water. The project cost a total of 900 million
yuan (108 million US dollars), one-third of which came from the
central government.
</P>
<P>
Over the past five years, the central government has
appropriated tens of billions yuan to a number of key projects in
Xinjiang, including a crude oil and petroleum chemical base,
cotton production centers and water conservation, railway and
airport projects.
</P>
<P>
Each year, the autonomous region receives more than 6.5 billion
yuan (783 million US dollars) of fiscal subsidies from the central
government. Over the past five years, Xinjiang has attracted 4.7
billion yuan (566 million US dollars) from other areas of the
country.
</P>
<P>
"We also implemented the policy of freedom in religious belief
and protect the legitimate rights and interests of believers," the
chairman said.
</P>
<P>
In Xinjiang, there are more than 28,000 clergies with some
20,000 mosques and 4,000 scripture recitation sites. The number of
mosques for every 10,000 moslems is higher than that in any Arab
countries.
</P>
<P>
"We will continue to implement the Law on Regional Autonomy for
China's Minority Nationalities in real earst, so as to consolidate
the equal, united and mutually-beneficial relationships between
ethnic groups," the official said.
</P>
<P>
Ablait was born into a common family. His father was a shoe
maker.
</P>
<P>
I never dreamed that I could attend college, become an
engineer, serve as chairman of the Xinjiang regional people's
government and act as an NPC chairman," he said. "Because China
carries out the policy of ethnic equality, unity and common
prosperity, and the central government pays attention to selecting
officials from among minority ethnic groups."
</P>
<P>
In the government departments of Xinjiang, officials from
minority ethnic groups account for 60 percent of the total.
</P>
<P>
Ablait said friends and businessmen from overseas are welcome
to Xinjiang to acquaint themselves with local realities.  
</P>
