<DOCNO> XIE19980308.0128 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Backgrounder: System of Provincial Governors Assuming Responsibility for "Rice Bag" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 8 (Xinhua) -- Following is an explanation of the
system of provincial governors assuming responsibility for the
"rice bag", a term mentioned in Chinese Premier Li Peng's
government work report to the First Session of the Ninth National
People's Congress.
</P>
<P>
To ensure stable supplies of grain, the central government
requires that the government heads of provinces, autonomous
regions and centrally-administered municipalities assume the
responsibility of maintaining grain supplies for their respective
areas.
</P>
<P>
Specifically, a governor must see to it that his or her
province:
</P>
<P>
-- Keeps a stable area of grain fields and a grain reserve
level meeting demand, and increases grain yield;
</P>
<P>
-- Fulfills a grain purchase target and a grain and cook oil
reserve plan set by the central government, and local grain
purchase plans;
</P>
<P>
-- Establishes a local risk fund for grain reserve;
</P>
<P>
-- Meets the target for inter-province grain flow target set by
the central government if the province is a major grain producer,
or fulfills the target of importing grain or buying grain from
other provinces if the province is not self-sufficient in grain
supply. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980308.0129 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Backgrounder: System of City Mayors Assuming Responsibility for "Vegetable Basket" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
To ease strains on the supply of vegetables and foodstuffs,
China's Ministry of Agriculture initiated the so-called "vegetable
basket project" in 1988, which aims to: improve production and
marketing of vegetables and foodstuffs, develop and utilize land
resources rationally, adjust the structure of supply and demand of
such products, popularize production techniques, and improve basic
facilities, all for the purpose of increasing the supplies of
vegetables and foodstuffs.
</P>
<P>
The central government requires that mayors shoulder the
responsibility of properly filling residents' baskets with
vegetables and foodstuffs, to make a success of the project.
</P>
<P>
From 1988 to 1996, the output of meat, dairy products, eggs,
aquatic products, fruits and vegetables increased remarkably,
helping to improve the standard of living of urban people.
</P>
<P>
Last year, the average amount of meat, aquatic products,
vegetables and the average number of eggs available for each
Chinese reached or exceeded the world's average.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
