<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Toshiba Disqualified from Whitbread 5th leg </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, March 8 (Xinhua) -- The yacht Toshiba has been
disqualified from the fifth leg of the Whitbread Round the World
Race after the engine was used to clear weed from the keel and
rudder, according to reports from Sao Sebastiao, Brazil.
</P>
<P>
A five-man international jury heard a protest by the race
committee, and found that the crew of Toshiba had started their
engine, breaking the seals on the propeller shaft, and failed to
report their actions to the race organisers at the right time.
</P>
<P>
The boat had finished the leg in sixth place, and was lying
fifth overall in the race, but this disqualification drops Toshiba
to sixth place overall in the race.
</P>
<P>
Benefiting from Toshiba's misfortune is the Norwegian entry
Innovation Kvaerner, skippered by Knut Frostad, which moved up to
sixth place for the leg, and fifth place overall.
</P>
<P>
The fifth leg of the Whitbread Round the World Race was a 6,670
mile trip from Auckland to Sao Sebastiao in Brazil, via the
Southern Ocean and Cape Horn. 
</P>
</TEXT>
