<HEADLINE> Hakkinen Wins Formula One Australian Grand Prix </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, March 8 (Xinhua) -- McLaren driver Mika Hakkinen of
Finland won the Australian Grand Prix over 58 laps on the
5.269-kilometer Albert Park circuit in Melbourne on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Teammate David Coulthard of Britain let Hakkinen through with
two laps remaining to finish second. Hakkinen finished in one
hour, 31 minutes and 45.996 seconds.
</P>
<P>
The McLarens were so dominant that both lapped third-placed
Williams driver Heinz-Harald Frentzen of Germany .
</P>
<P>
Defending Formula One champion Jacques Villeneuve of Canada was
fifth in the second Williams while former champion Michael
Schumacher of Germany lasted just five laps in his Ferrari.
</P>
</TEXT>
