<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Normal Gas Supply Resumes in Dhaka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, March 8 (Xinhua) -- Residents here heaved a sigh of
relief as normal gas supply resumed in the city Saturday ending a
three-day-long disruption.
</P>
<P>
Workers and engineers completed the repair Saturday morning,
after the damaged gas transmission line 22 feet down the surface
at Rampura was located on Friday midnight, reports said.
</P>
<P>
More than half of the city plunged into an unprecedented gas
crisis Thursday morning, when a construction company drove a pile
on a 12-inch diameter high-pressure main transmission line during
the construction work of a residential building of Bangladesh
Television, near Rampura TV complex, and city dwellers found their
stoves were out of gas in the afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Some 300 workers, engineers and officials worked
round-the-clock to repair the pipeline. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
