<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Serb Anti-Terrorist Police Kill 40 "Terrorists" in Kosovo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, March 7 (Xinhua) -- Serbian anti-terrorist police
units killed 40 "terrorists" and captured some weapons during
recent offensives against ethnic Albanian separatists in Kosovo, a
Serbian official said Saturday in Pristina, capital of Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
Ljubinko Cvetich, spokesman for the Ministry of Interior, told
a news conference that among those killed was Adem Jassari, an
alleged separatist leader.
</P>
<P>
Cvetich also said that from 1991 to March 5, 1998, ethnic
Albanian separatists had launched 200 terrorist activities,
killing 9 policemen and 24 civilians.
</P>
<P>
Terrorism in Kosovo was on a rise in the two years, he added.
</P>
<P>
Serbian police this week attacked the alleged Kosovo Liberation
Army (KLA) bastions of Prekaz and Lausha in the mountains of
central Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
The KLA emerged as a military threat in response to growing
impatience with the lack of progress made by political leaders
demanding independence for Kosovo, where 90 percent of the 1.8
million population are ethnic Albanians. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
