<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Senior Chinese Officers on Army Building and Reform </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 8 (Xinhua) -- Some military deputies to the
First Session of the Ninth National People's Congress (NPC) said
the Chinese army will hold high Deng Xiaoping Theory and safeguard
the authority of Communist Party of China (CPC) Central Committee
with Jiang Zemin at the core in the new historical period.
</P>
<P>
Fu Quanyou, Yu Yongbo, Wang Ke and Wang Ruilin, all members of
the Central Military Commission (CMC), said at the panel
discussion of the People's Liberation Army (PLA) delegation that
to comply with the command of the CPC Central Committee and the
CMC is the guarantee for scoring new victories of China's
socialist cause.
</P>
<P>
Under the new situation in the new period, the army will act as
a powerful guarantee for China's reform, opening-up and
modernization drive, Fu Quanyou said.
</P>
<P>
In army building, emphasis should be placed on training
qualified personnel, managing the army with strict rules,
developing high-tech weaponry and military equipment in an effort
to raise the fighting competence at the modern times, he said.
</P>
<P>
Yu Yongbo said all officers and men should be distinctly aware
of the importance of serving the country's overall task and
supporting reform, and have adopted firm attitude in this regard.
</P>
<P>
On the occasion of streamlining and readjusting the PLA,
disciplines must be emphasized so that individuals should be
submitted to organizations and local units are to the overall
situation, he said.
</P>
<P>
In following the overall task of China's economic growth, Wang
Ke said, army building should be carried out with thrift.
Logistical departments of the army should enhance management and
reform so as to raise the efficiency of logistical supply, he
added.
</P>
<P>
In particular, leading officers and military departments, which
are vested with power financially, materially and in management of
related affairs should play an exemplary role in army building
through thrift, he said.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, Wang Ruilin said, in streamlining the army and taking
the path of fewer but better troops, leading officers should be
models in carrying on the army's fine traditions of hard work,
opposing extravagance and guarding against and preventing any
corrosion of corruption and degeneration. 
</P>
</TEXT>
