<HEADLINE> Agriculture Highlighted in NPC Discussion (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Deputy Deng Jian, a prefecture commissioner from Sichuan,
another big agriculture province, said he is worried about China's
still weak agriculture foundation, emphasizing that the government
should always give the first priority to agriculture and rural
work.
</P>
<P>
Deputy Wang Yulin, director of Heilongjiang Land Reclamation
Bureau, said he supports the establishment of an agriculture and
rural affairs committee under the NPC Standing Committee, adding
the committee could play a great role in solving existing problems
in agriculture.
</P>
<P>
"Hopefully, agriculture-related legislation will be
accelerated," he said. "This will allow key policy measures to be
written down in the form of laws and be implemented through law
enforcement and supervision."
</P>
<P>
Wang is confident that the committee will play an important
role in increasing agriculture input, sorting out the pricing
system for farm produce, and improving the grain sales structure.
</P>
<P>
Deputy Wang Weiyi, a professor from Nanjing Agriculture
University, expressed the hope that the newly established
committee will help better implement the farmland contracting
policy, ease farmers' financial burdens, promote the use of
agriculture-related science and technology and protect
eco-environment in agriculture.
</P>
<P>
The move, he said, will boost farmers' enthusiasm in farm
production while protecting their intermediate interests. "It will
benefit the long-term development of rural areas," he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
