<HEADLINE> Chernomyrdin Calls on Russians to Pay Income Tax </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, March 7 (Xinhua) -- Russian Prime Minister Viktor
Chernomyrdin Saturday called upon Russian citizens to pay their
income tax voluntarily.
</P>
<P>
He said that since all the tax revenues will be used to meet
the need of local budgets, it is the citizens themselves who will
get the most benefits.
</P>
<P>
Chernomyrdin made the appeal in answering questions from
Russian TV audiences. A government spokesman said that the prime
minister will appear in the question-and-answer program every
Saturday evening.
</P>
<P>
The prime minister said that he has filled out his own tax form
and that all government officials will make public their income
tax forms as they did last year.
</P>
<P>
On prospect of his running for the presidency in 2000,
Chernomyrdin said that he is not considering the question for the
time being. Instead he is considering how to improve the living
standard of the Russian people. 
