<HEADLINE> Socialist Party Likely to Win Election: Hungarian PM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUDAPEST, March 7 (Xinhua) -- The ruling Socialist Party has
demonstrated its governing capability in the past four years and
is likely to win parliamentary elections in May, Hungarian Premier
Horn Gyula said here Saturday.
</P>
<P>
At a meeting of the Socialist Party, Horn said that the Party
would not share power with any opposition parties if it wins the
elections.
</P>
<P>
It would continue its cooperation with the Alliance of Free
Democrats (AFD), he said.
</P>
<P>
The coalition government had created conditions for Hungary's
economy to develop steadily, Horn said. Despite the two parties'
differences, their representatives shared the same value, which
would guarantee the realization of the country's major interests
under their administration.
</P>
<P>
The meeting of the Socialist Party, which started Saturday, had
unanimously adopted its campaign program.
</P>
<P>
Horn was elected the candidate for the prime minister after a
closed-door voting.
</P>
<P>
The elections of the Hungarian National Assembly were to be
held in May.
</P>
<P>
According to a recent opinion poll, the Socialist Party enjoys
the highest popularity. 
</P>
