The Colombian Coffee Growers National Committee made the
decision Friday after rains in the coffee producing zones
dispelled drought fears of the consuming countries.
</P>
<P>
Coffee buyers had feared that a dearth of the product in the
market would be caused by the drought brought about by "El Nino"
phenomenon. 
