<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hu Jintao on Development of Central and Western Regions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 8 (Xinhua) -- Senior Chinese Party official Hu
Jintao today urged officials and people in the less-developed
central and western regions to improve their understanding of
economic regularities and seek a rapid and sound development.
</P>
<P>
Hu, a member of the Standing Committee of the Political Bureau
of the Communist Party of China's Central Committee, made these
remarks during a panel discussion with the delegation to the
ongoing session of the Ninth National People's Congress from
southwest China's Guizhou Province.
</P>
<P>
"The current situation provides very good opportunities for the
reform, opening-up and growth of the central and western regions.
As long as we give full play to the local advantages and work hard
with confidence, the central and western regions are full of
hopes," he said.
</P>
<P>
He urged people in Guizhou to increase their awareness of the
regularities in local economic growth and focus on solving major
problems that hinder the province's development.
</P>
<P>
He put forth suggestions for Guizhou on agricultural growth,
poverty alleviation, infrastructure construction and adjustment of
the ownership structure.
</P>
<P>
"We must go in for the reform of large and medium-sized
state-owned enterprises on one hand, and further ease controls on
small state enterprises to increase their vitality on the other
hand," he noted.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, he said, it is also essential to encourage and
support the growth of non-public economy if Guizhou wants to
attain its goal of development and solve the problem of
re-employment of laid-off workers.
</P>
<P>
He also underlined the importance of training a contingent of
highly-competent leading officials, especially Party and
government leaders at the county (city) level, for the development
of the central and western regions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
