<HEADLINE> Russia to Reduce 300,000 Military Officers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, March 7 (Xinhua) -- In a major step to streamline its
armed forces, Russia plans to reduce 300,000 military officers
this year, Interfax news agency has reported.
</P>
<P>
According to Russian military sources, the cut-down will begin
with military administrative organs such as the general staff and
headquarters of various services.
</P>
<P>
The staff of these management organs will be reduced by 30
percent between May and the end of this year, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, more than 40 military colleges and universities will
be closed down, retiring as many as about 15,000 graduates this
year.
</P>
<P>
Under a military reform plan proposed last year, the Russian
armed forces will be reduced from 1.7 million to 1.2 million in
the first phase of reform from 1997 to 2000. 
</P>
</TEXT>
