<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Today is Macao Tomorrow: Macao NPC Deputies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 8 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's smooth return on July
1 last year and its steady growth in the subsequent eight months
have greatly increased Macao people's confidence in the good
prospects for Macao after its own return to the motherland in
1999.
</P>
<P>
These consensus was reached here today by deputies from Macao
to the Ninth National People's Congress (NPC), the country's top
legislature which is now in its first annual session.
</P>
<P>
The deputies agreed that the smooth return of Hong Kong and
Macao, which signifies a great success for the "one country, two
systems" concept initiated by the late leader Deng Xiaoping, would
add impetus to the ultimate accomplishment of the great cause of
China's peaceful reunification.
</P>
<P>
"Hong Kong has returned, and Macao will soon come back too. I
have been staying in the two places for more than 70 years, and I
was in a most happy mood in the past several years," said O
Ching-ping, who is approaching 90 and has been elected to the NPC
for the sixth time.
</P>
<P>
Edmund Hau Wah Ho, vice-chairman of the Macao Chinese General
Chamber of Commerce, said that the smooth return of Hong Kong can
serve as a vivid example for Macao.
</P>
<P>
"It has become a common understanding among the Macao people
that Hong Kong today is Macao tomorrow. With the powerful backing
of the motherland, Macao will have brighter prospects in the next
century," he noted.
</P>
<P>
The most crucial and urgent work at present is to set up the
Preparatory Committee for the Macao Special Administrative Region
(SAR), he acknowledged.
</P>
<P>
Deputy Tong Seng Chiu, president of the Federation of Trade
Unions of Macao, said the masses of workers in Macao love the
country and their home, and have shown great concerns about the
return in 1999.
</P>
<P>
"We all hope that the SAR Preparatory Committee will be founded
at an early date, to lay a solid foundation for various work in
the transitional period and the operation of the future SAR
government," he noted.
</P>
<P>
Macao has five Ninth NPC deputies, who have joined in the
Guangdong delegation to the current session. 
</P>
</TEXT>
