<HEADLINE> Shaanxi Guides Foreign Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, March 8 (Xinhua) -- Northwest China's Shaanxi Province,
which has been fortified by the use of foreign investment in
economic development in west and central China, has drafted new
policies guiding the further introduction of overseas funds during
1998.
</P>
<P>
The province plans to attract overseas investment from an
expanded number of channels, and will at the same time improve the
use of related funding.
</P>
<P>
The major proportion of related funds will be earmarked for
improving local water supplies, highway construction and the
overall improvement of deteriorating urban areas.
</P>
<P>
Major projects earmarked for increased foreign investment will
include a number of basic industries, such as the energy and raw
materials sectors, as well as the efficient agricultural industry
engaged in the development and the deep-processing of farm and
sideline products.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the expected influx of foreign funds will focus on
technological upgrading of state-owned enterprises, and on
development of the tourism and various aspects of the high-tech
sector involving electronic information processing and
biochemicals. 
</P>
