<HEADLINE> Lazutina Takes over World Cup Lead </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HELSINKI, March 7 (Xinhua) -- Stefania Belmondo of Italy won
Saturday's women's 15-kilometer freestyle at the Lahti Nordic
World Cup Ski Games Saturday while runner-up Larisa Lazutina of
Russia took the World Cup lead from Bente Martinsen of Norway.
</P>
<P>
Belmondo finished the course in 38 minutes, 49.3 seconds, 10.2
seconds ahead of Lazutina. But Lazutina, who entered the race
trailing by 38 points in the World Cup standings, increased her
total to 573, with Belmondo a solid third with 459 points.
</P>
<P>
In ski jumping (K120) event, Janne Ahonen of Finland scored
259.7 points for the top place while Andy Widholzl of Austria
finished second with 258.3 points.
</P>
<P>
Ahonen, 20, won his first title of season in his hometown with
jumps of 125 and 121 meters. Widholzl's results of the two jumps
were 124.5 and 121 meters.
</P>
<P>
Bjarte Engen Vik of Norway topped the World Cup standings with
a total of 1,175 points and Austrian Mario Stecher came second
with 1,065 points. 
</P>
