<HEADLINE> Chinese Bank Grants Loans for Fujian Highway </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, March 8 (Xinhua) -- The China Construction Bank (CCB),
one of the nation's four major commercial banks, recently granted
a 500 million yuan loan for the construction of a highway project
from Fuzhou city to Quanzhou city in east China's Fujian Province.
</P>
<P>
The 166-km Fuzhou-Quanzhou Highway, one of the most important
infrastructure projects in Fujian province during the 1996-2000
period, will be constructed at a total cost of 4.7 billion
yuan. The highway is scheduled to open on October 1, 1999.
</P>
<P>
The local government has raised four billion yuan for the
project, and is currently seeking additional bank loans totalling
700 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
CCB's Credit and Loan Administration Committee approved the
aforementioned loan of 500 million yuan. The recent loan is in
addition to some 200 million yuan in loans previously granted by
the bank. 
</P>
</TEXT>
