<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Guangzhou Attaches Greater Importance to Reemployment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, March 8 (Xinhua) -- Labor departments in Guangzhou,
capital of south China's Guangdong Province, have adopted a series
of reemployment measures to ensure that this year's unemployment
level remains below three percent.
</P>
<P>
The measures include the introduction of a records system
clearly listing the number of people laid off, regulating
enterprises contemplating staff reductions and placing
restrictions on enterprises to prevent said reductions for
unjustified economic reasons.
</P>
<P>
Reemployment service centers are being established in sectors
and enterprises subject to high lay-off rates in order to transfer
workers to the private and service sectors. Plans also call for
the establishment of an unemployment insurance system.
</P>
<P>
Labor departments have established a special fund of 80 million
yuan to be used for retraining and providing new job
opportunities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
