<HEADLINE> Fontaine Wins Second World Cup Freestyle Skiing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, March 7 (Xinhua) -- World Cup champion Nicolas Fontaine
of Canada on Saturday snatched his second victory of the season in
Meiringen and the top spot in the World Cup freestyle aerials
rankings.
</P>
<P>
In the women's event Australia's Jacqui Cooper won her third
consecutive World Cup event, beating Olympic champion Nikki Stone
of the United States into second place.
</P>
<P>
Fontaine, whose last victory dates back to the season opener,
won with 239.36 points. Alexei Grichin of Belarus finished second
with 238.42 and Germany's Gerhard Melcher was third with 226.76.
</P>
<P>
Fontaine's victory moved him to the top of the aerials
standings with 580 points, ahead of countryman Andy Capicik with
544 and American Britt Swartley with 528.
</P>
<P>
Cooper won the women's event with 177.87 points.
</P>
<P>
Stone, who has four World Cup victories this season, finished
second with 176.54, but remained atop the aerials standings with
592 points ahead of Cooper, second with 584.
</P>
<P>
Switzerland's Michele Rohrbach was third with 168.43.  
</P>
</TEXT>
