<HEADLINE> Brazilian Scherer Shines in Swimming World Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, March 7 (Xinhua) -- Brazilian Fernando Scherer
shattered his South American record for the 50-meter butterfly at
a World Cup swimming meet in Rio de Janeiro Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Scherer touched home in 23.97 seconds, beating his previous
mark of 24.15, set in March 1995.
</P>
<P>
He was three-tenths of a second ahead of Dutchman Joris Keizer
who finished second, and 0.35 ahead of Denys Silantiev of the
Ukraine.
</P>
<P>
Dutchman Marcel Wouda was the overall men's star, winning three
events. Wouda took the 400m individual medley in 4:15.68, the 200m
breaststroke in 2:11.67 and the 100m individual medley in 55.31.
</P>
<P>
Antje Buschchulte of Germany and Claudia Poll of Costa Rica
each won two women's events. 
</P>
