<DOCNO> XIE19980308.0208 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Guangzhou Improves Social Security System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, March 8 (Xinhua) -- Guangzhou, capital of south
China's Guangdong Province, has improved its social security
system based on old-age pension and unemployment insurance.
</P>
<P>
The past 12 years of reform has witnessed the evolution of
Guangzhou's social security system from simply enterprise
insurance to actual social insurance. Proposed regulations on
worker's medical compensation insurance will be issued by the end
of 1998.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that some 710,000 workers were covered by
old-age pension insurance by the end of last year, including some
400,000 retirees.
</P>
<P>
Guangzhou established its social security bureau in 1996 as
part of an effort to strengthen the unified management of social
security.
</P>
<P>
However, a city official noted that the existing social
security system mostly covers people with ties to state-owned
enterprises. Most employees from foreign-funded and private
enterprises are not as yet covered by the city's social security
system.
</P>
<P>
The Guangzhou government has set a 1998 goal of expanding
coverage of the social security system, and will place special
emphasis on issuing detailed regulations governing employees from
private and rural enterprises. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
