<HEADLINE> Czech, Swede Lead Park World Tour '98 Orienteering Series </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 7 (Xinhua) -- Last year's overall champions
Rudolf Ropek from Czech Republic and Gunilla Svard from Sweden
came out temporary leaders for the men's and women's divisions
after the first two races of the 750,000 HK dollars (9,610
U.S. dollars), 10-race orienteering series here on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Ropek, third placer in the opening race on Friday, finished
first in the 2.4-kilometer second race on Saturday, with a time of
12 minutes 48 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Denmark's Chris Terkelsen followed in 12:50 and his compatriot
Allan Mogensen was third in 13:18.
</P>
<P>
In the women's race, Austrian Lucie Bohm, who finished third in
the opening stage on Friday, covered the same course in 14:32, one
hundredth of a second ahead Sweden's Gunilla Svard.
</P>
<P>
Heather Monro of Britain and Australian Mary Fein tied for
third place with identical times of 15:35.
</P>
<P>
Competitors will proceed to Beijing for the two races in the
second leg of the Tour, set for March 14-15. The six remaining
races will be held in various European cities from May to August.
</P>
<P>
This is the first time any Park World Tour races are held in
Asia. Competing in the series are the world's top 50 male and
female orienteers from 19 countries and regions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
